def: A febrile disease characterized by dyspnoa and bronchitiscaused by inhaling dust.
That which remains; a remnant; a residue.
A degeneration of animal tissue into a cheesy or curdy mass.
One who disbelieves, or refuses belief; an unbeliever.Specifically, one who does not believe the Christian religion. I.Watts.

A marble mausoleum built at Agra, India, by the Mogul EmperorShah Jahan, in memory of his favorite wife. In beauty of design andrich decorative detail it is one of the best examples of Saracenicarchitecture.
The act of suffixing, or the state of being suffixed.
Of or pertaining to Eden; paradisaic. "Edenic joys." Mrs.Browning.
Marriage only within the tribe; a custom restricting a man inhis choice of a wife to the tribe to which he belongs; -- opposed toexogamy.
Greaves; armor for the legs. [Obs.] Spenser.
One who, or that which, weeds, or frees from anything noxious.
Indistinct; slurred over. [Obs.] "Obscure and oblite mention."Fuller.
